&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com, Igor Ranitovic &lt;igor@a...&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt; Hi Jay,
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; We could not figure out any combination of existing scopes and
&gt; filters that will accomplish this.
&gt; &gt; Therefore, you will need to write a new scope for this purpose.
&gt; &gt; The idea is to accept all URIs that fall into one of these two
&gt; categories:
&gt; &gt;       - URI in the scope (domain, host, and etc.)
&gt; &gt;          - URI not in the scope but URI&#39;s via in the scope
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; This should allow you +1 hop crawling and should not be hard to
&gt; implement.
&gt; &gt; Maybe something like this (host scope +1 hop away):
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; public class HostPlusOneScope extends HostScope {
&gt; &gt;      public HostPlusOneScope(String name) {
&gt; &gt;          super(name);
&gt; &gt;          setDescription(&quot;HostPlusOne&quot;);
&gt; &gt;      }
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;      protected boolean focusAccepts(Object o) {
&gt; &gt;          UURI u = getUURI(o);
&gt; &gt;          if (u == null) {
&gt; &gt;              return false;
&gt; &gt;          }
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;          Iterator iter = seedsIterator();
&gt; &gt;          while(iter.hasNext()) {
&gt; &gt;              // Check if in host scope
&gt; &gt;              if (isSameHost((UURI)iter.next(), u)){
&gt; &gt;                      return true;
&gt; &gt;              }
&gt; &gt;              // URI not in host scope, check via URI
&gt; &gt;              UURI via = getVia(o);
&gt; &gt;              if (via != null && isSameHost(((UURI)iter.next()), via)){
&gt; &gt;                  return true;
&gt; &gt;              }
&gt; &gt;          }
&gt; &gt;          return false;
&gt; &gt;      }
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;      private UURI getVia(Object o){
&gt; &gt;          if (o instanceof CandidateURI) {
&gt; &gt;              return ((CandidateURI) o).getVia();
&gt; &gt;          }
&gt; &gt;          return null;
&gt; &gt;      }
&gt; &gt; }
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; If you want to write a scope that will do +N hops away, then it will
&gt; be a bit more complicated since
&gt; &gt; you will need extra tracking of not-in-scope URIs.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Let us if we can help more.
&gt; &gt; i.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; P.S.
&gt; &gt; 1. LowercaseRule changes the entire URI string to lowercase.
&gt; &gt; 2. max-refferal-hops limits crawling of redirects that are out of scope.
